Geographic distribution.

Pseudopaludicola hyleaustralis

is known from four localities in the northern state of Mato Grosso, 
Brazil
(municipalities of Colniza, Alta Floresta, Nova Bandeirantes, and Aripuanã), along the drainages of the Apiacás, Roosevelt and Aripuanã rivers (

Figure 
1

).
